HEADWORD: Hydrachnid
<hw>Hy*drach"nid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hydr-</ets>
+ ar<ets>achnid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An aquatic mite of
the genus <gen>Hydrachna</gen>. The hydrachnids, while young, are
parasitic on fresh-water mussels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydracid</ent>⟦br⟧
